entry.content:
Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: pizza to North Korea (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Kim Jong Il had Italian chefs flown into Pyongyang to introduce pizza to North Korea (example pictured)?

entry.title: Church of St John of the Collachium (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Church of St John of the Collachium was said to contain the hand of John the Baptist, a bowl used by Jesus, and a piece of the True Cross?

entry.title: LA LOM (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that LA LOM named many of their songs after various locations in Los Angeles?

entry.title: Nuwhaha (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Nuwhaha people, despite sometimes being erroneously known as the "Upper Samish", do not speak the Samish language?

entry.title: Betty Hanley (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Betty Hanley, originally a Michigander, was appointed lampshade designer to the British royal family?

entry.title: Motokare Retry (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the spin-off episode of the live-action adaptation of Motokare Retry was written to portray "conversations between men" and "male friendship"?

entry.title: United States Pavilion (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that during the 1964 New York World's Fair, police officers used computers at the United States Pavilion to help arrest people?

entry.title: Qupanuk Olsen (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Greenlandic content creator Qupanuk Olsen petitioned the Inatsisartut to move Greenland's time zone to UTC−03:00?
